						<div class="postbody">Really, I need help. I rewrote the PPU timing code and the problem persists.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">Zepper wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- It seems the same problem with this <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5468&amp;highlight=midscanline+demo" class="postlink">demo by Bregalad</a>.<br /><br /><img src="http://img714.imageshack.us/img714/7791/midscanlineb000.png" alt="Image" /></div>
<br />
<br />This glitch occurs in my emulator at the pre-rendered scanline, since the PPU frame can be 1 cycle shorter in odd frames (340). It can be "fixed" if manually setting up the number of cycles to 339 for the pre-rendered scanline.</div>

					
