						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What are the timestamps (in ppu pixels) for the relevant bankswitch or ppu control instructions?</div>
<br />
<br /><a href="http://rocknes.net/midscanline_timestamp.zip" class="postlink">Here.</a> (6kb)
<br />
<br />The first hexa number with 4 digits is the PPU address (loopy_v) used.
<br />
<br />L = scanline number, my 1st visible scanline is 21, VBlank starts at scanline zero.
<br />C = PPU cycle (or dot).
<br />
<br />I included the frame number and its situation: good (no glitches) and bad. The 12nd frame is good.</div>

					
